cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the normalization of journal impact factors to make them comparable between scientific fields. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, given the focus on citation behaviour and publication patterns, we believe that cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
